snippet.textDisplay: I love both of these guys...such humble gentlemen! Unfortunately the massive weight gain on Fury will do him in. He's gained weight to add more power to his shots but he'll definitely sacrifice speed and endurance over the long haul. Having weight doesn't mean you can absorb punishment nor add to punching power (maybe a slight 3-4%increase) I would have kept Fury lean and fast to be able to move and counter and beat wilder to the punch. Instead he just became a massive target. Wilder on the other hand looks strong and healthy. He added 10+ pounds of muscle which will add to his power, he'll be able to absorb a bit more and he might have a slight speed increase. I predict Wilder for the win either by knock out in the 8th or a unanimous decision. If its a draw (which i could be) it'll set up for a trilogy that the whole world would want to watch, leaving Anthony Joshua hanging in the wind
